@NODE FM_PAGE
@TITLE "Project/Page Setup..."
@TOC Main
@PREV PM_SAVE_AS
@NEXT SM_OUTPUTAREA

@{u}@{b}Menu Item:	Project/Page Setup...@{ub}@{uu}

@{u}Command Key:	Right_Amiga-P@{uu}

	Choosing the @{b}Project/Page Setup...@{ub} menu item opens the Page Setup
requester.  Use this requestor to change the page layout attributes of the
current project.


/****** THE HELP FILES HAVE BEEN ABRIDGED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/

@ENDNODE


@NODE SM_OUTPUTAREA
@TITLE "Project/Define Output Area"
@TOC Main
@PREV FM_PAGE
@NEXT PM_IMPORT

@{b}@{u}Menu Item:	Project/Define Output Area@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	The @{b}Project/Define Output Area@{ub} menu item lets you specify a portion
of the current project for output.  The default output area is the full
page.

	The area of the drawing outside the delimited section will not be
printed, while the output area will be proportionally scaled to fit the
dimensions of the output device page.  You will have the option of turning
off this scaling when using the PostScript driver.

	This feature is most useful for making enlarged printouts of details
of your drawing.  It may also be used for indicating the non-printable
margins of your paper when printing to Preferences printers.


/****** THE HELP FILES HAVE BEEN ABRIDGED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/

@ENDNODE


@NODE PM_IMPORT
@TITLE "The Project/Import Sub-Menu"
@TOC Main
@PREV SM_OUTPUTAREA
@NEXT PM_FPLOT

@{b}@{u}Menu Item:	Project/Import  ╗@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	The @{b}Project/Import  ╗@{ub} sub-menu lists the different file formats that
ProVector« can load.  There will always be at least three items in the
sub-menu:

	@{" External.. " link PM_EXTERNAL} - Load module from other drive/device
	@{" DR2D...    " link PM_DR2D} - Import another drawing into the current project
	@{" ILBM...    " link PM_BITMAP} - Import an IFF-ILBM bitmap into the current project

	These three functions are built into ProVector.  Additional sub-menu
items may be present, depending on whether you have any external import
modules installed.  Any import modules that ProVector finds in the PV_Import
drawer at startup will automatically be added to the @{b}Project/Import  ╗@{ub}
sub-menu.

@{u}External Import Modules@{uu}

	@{" HPGLImport " link PV_Import.guide/HPGL} -  Import HP-GL, commonly used by plotters & sign-cutters
	@{" PSImport   " link PV_Import.guide/PostScript} -  Import PostScript, EPS, Illustrator, etc.

/****** THE HELP FILES HAVE BEEN ABRIDGED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/

@ENDNODE


@NODE PM_EXTERNAL
@TITLE "Project/Import/External..."
@TOC Main
@PREV PM_IMPORT
@NEXT PM_DR2D

@{b}@{u}Sub-Menu Item:	Project/Import/External...@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	Choosing the @{b}Project/Import/External...@{ub} sub-menu item opens the file
requester to load an import module located in some directory or device
other than the standard PV_Import drawer.

	Once you select the module's file name, the module will load and
display its requester just like any of the modules found in the PV_Import
drawer.

	See @{" Export Drivers " link PV_IMport.guide/Main} for specifics on the individual drivers.

	See @{" Project/Open... " link Provector.guide/PM_OPEN} for more details on the file requester.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PM_DR2D
@TITLE "Project/Import/DR2D..."
@TOC Main
@PREV PM_EXTERNAL
@NEXT PM_BITMAP

@{b}@{u}Sub-Menu Item:	Project/Import/DR2D...@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	Choosing the @{b}Project/Import/DR2D...@{ub} sub-menu item will open a file
requester similar to the @{" Project/Open... " link ProVector.guide/PM_OPEN} menu item.  However, instead of
opening the selected DR2D file as a separate project, the drawing will be
inserted into the current project window.

	The objects of the imported drawing will assume the corresponding
colors and fill patterns of the current project's palette.  The palette of
the imported drawing is ignored.  Thus, an object with solid fill #2 (pure
red in the default palette) will assume the RGB (Red, Blue, Green) color
values of color #2 in the importing drawing.  The importing drawing might
have a custom palette where color #2 has been modified to a burgundy rather
than a pure red.

	This is similar to the handling of color assignments when objects
are pasted between projects with the clipboard.  See @{" Edit/Paste " link ProVector.guide/EM_PASTE} for
details.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PM_BITMAP
@TITLE "Project/Import/ILBM..."
@TOC Main
@PREV PM_DR2D
@NEXT PM_FPLOT

@{b}@{u}Sub-Menu Item:	Project/Import/ILBM...@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	Choose the @{b}Project/Import/ILBM...@{ub} sub-menu item to load a bitmap
into the current project.  After the file requester opens, select a standard
(IFF-ILBM) bitmap file, just as you would any other file. The bitmap will be
displayed in the project.

	The image can be thus be incorporated into your composition for
output to various formats, or traced with ProVector drawing tools to create
a structured (and thus, resolution independent) version of the image.  In
the second case, the original bitmap can then be deleted with the @{" Delete " link ProVector.guide/EM_DELETE}
tool to save memory.

	All of the Object Manipulation tools with the exceptions of the
@{" Rotate " link ProVector.guide/OM_ROTATE} tool and the @{" Change " link ProVector.guide/OM_CHANGE} tool will operate on a bitmap.  Furthermore,
you may mask the bitmap using the @{" Edit/Paste Inside " link EM_PASTEIN}

	The bitmap itself is not saved in the project file.  Only the
directory path/filename of the bitmap will be stored in the DR2D (project)
file.  The bitmap can then be looked up, and reloaded when the project is
reloaded.

	See @{" Project/Open... " link ProVector.guide/PM_OPEN} for more details on the file requester.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PM_FPLOT
@TITLE "The Project/Export Sub-Menu"
@TOC Main
@PREV PM_IMPORT
@NEXT PM_CLOSE

@{b}@{u}Menu Item:	Project/Export  ╗@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}


/****** EXPORTING HAS BEEN DISABLED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/


	The @{b}Project/Export/External...@{ub} sub-menu item opens a file requester
for loading an output driver that is not installed in the PV_Drivers drawer.

	All of the available ProVector output options are implemented as
external drivers that are only loaded when needed.  This saves both memory
and disk space for users who rarely or never need all of the output options
ProVector provides.

	See @{" Overview of Printing, Etc. " link PV_Export.guide/ExportOver} for general information on
ProVector output.  See @{" External Drivers " link PV_Export.guide/Main} for information on the use of
specific drivers.

	These drivers are normally stored in the PV_Drivers drawer.  At
startup time, ProVector will look in this drawer, and automatically con-
figure the @{b}Project/Export@{ub} sub-menu to list the available drivers.


/****** THE HELP FILES HAVE BEEN ABRIDGED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/

@ENDNODE


