@NODE OM_OBJ2FILL
@TITLE "Object/Obj to Fill"
@TOC OM_ATTRS
@PREV OM_ATTRS
@NEXT OM_FILL2OBJ

@{b}@{u}Menu Item:	Object/Obj to Fill...@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	Choose the @{b}Object/Obj to Fill@{ub} menu item to convert the currently
selected object or group of objects into a structured fill-pattern.  First
select a structured fill-pattern from the Fill requester.  Then create a
pattern.  If the pattern consists of more than one object, you must @{b}Group@{ub}
them.  Be sure the object or pattern is selected, then choose @{b}Obj to Fill@{ub}
from the @{b}Object@{ub} menu.  The current structured fill-pattern will be replaced
with the new pattern.

	Any existing objects filled with the old pattern will be refilled
with the new pattern.

	See also the @{" Object/Fill to Obj " link OM_FILL2OBJ} menu item.

@ENDNODE


@NODE OM_FILL2OBJ
@TITLE "Object/Fill to Obj"
@TOC Main
@PREV OM_OBJ2FILL
@NEXT  TM_TYPEFACE

@{b}@{u}Menu Item:	Object/Fill to Obj@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	Choose the @{b}Object/Fill to Obj@{ub} menu item to paste the currently
selected structured fill-pattern into the project window as a standard
ProVector object (the current fill attribute must be a structured-fill
pattern for this command to work).  This object may then be @{b}Ungroup@{ub}'ed,
edited and reassigned as a new fill pattern with the @{b}Obj to Fill@{ub} command.

	See also the @{" Object/Obj to Fill " link OM_OBJ2FILL} menu item.

@ENDNODE


