@TOC OM_PATH
@PREV OM_SPLIT
@NEXT OM_EFFECT

@{b}@{u}Sub-Menu Item:	Object/Path/Fit Curve@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	f@{uu}

	Choosing the @{b}Object/Path/Fit Curve@{ub} menu item alters the number of
points and curves that define the shape of selected objects; based on the
values in the @{b}Curve Tolerance@{ub} and @{b}Break Angle@{ub} numeric gadget in the
@{" Edit Prefs " link SM_EDIT} requester.

	This menu item can be used to simplify complex shapes (for instance
shapes that have too many points for a PostScript« printer to print
properly).

	The larger the value of the @{b}Curve Tolerance@{ub} setting the more
relaxed, or simplified, the objects will become.

@ENDNODE


