@NODE VM_LAYERS
@TITLE "View/Layers..."
@TOC Main
@PREV VM_GRID
@NEXT VM_RULERS

@{b}@{u}Menu Item:	View/Layers...@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Right_Amiga-L@{uu}

	Choose the @{b}View/Layers...@{ub} menu item to control the arragement and
status of layers in the current project.

	The largest and most important area in the requester is the list of
layers present in the project.  The layers are shown in the list in the same
order as they are displayed in the project. You may scroll through the list
by using the scroll bar to the right of the list.  The letters to the left
of each layer name signifies the status of the layer.  These letters may be
"C", "E", "L", or "H".  These signify "Current", "Edit", "Lock" and "Hide",
respectively.  The Current layer is that layer in which newly created
objects are placed.  An Editable layer allows objects in that layer to be
modified.  A Locked layer displayes the objects in the layer, but does not
allow the objects to be modified.  A Hidden layer is not displayed on the
screen at all.


/****** THE HELP FILES HAVE BEEN ABRIDGED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/

@ENDNODE


