@NODE UM_REXXECUTE
@TITLE "User/Rexxecute..."
@TOC Main
@PREV Main
@NEXT Main

@{b}@{u}Menu item:	User/Rexxecute...@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Command Key:	Not available@{uu}

	@{b}User/Rexxecute...@{ub} is the only fixed menu item in the @{b}User@{ub} menu.
Choosing this menu item opens a file requester listing the available ARexx
macros.  You may run a macro by selecting one from the list, then selecting
the @{b}OK@{ub} gadget or pressing the Return key.

	ProVector users can configure the @{b}User@{ub} menu with additional menu
items to call the ARexx macros of their choice.  See the ProVector @{" Define " link PVRX_Commands.guide/Define}
ARexx command.

The @{b}User@{ub} menu is preconfigured with several useful macros.


	@{" Available ARexx Macros   " link PVRX.guide/Main}
	@{" ProVector ARexx Commands " link PVRX_Commands.guide/Main}

/****** THE HELP FILES HAVE BEEN ABRIDGED FOR THIS DEMO RELEASE. ******/

@ENDNODE


@NODE Status
@TITLE "The Status Window"
@TOC Main
@PREV Main
@NEXT Main

@{b}@{u}The Status Window@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Function Key:	F2@{uu}

	The status window displays the @{b}Current Attributes@{ub}.  The Current
Attributes are the attributes (fill and line styles, colors, etc.) inherited
by newly created objects.

	The rectangle in the upper-left represents the current fill color,
and type (ie. @{b}Solid@{ub}, @{b}Gradient@{ub}, @{b}Pattern@{ub}, or @{b}No Fill@{ub}).

	The rectangle in the upper-right represents the current line color.

	The line beneath the color swatches is the current line pattern (ie.
@{b}Solid@{ub}, @{b}Dot@{ub}, @{b}Dash@{ub}, @{b}Dot-Das@{ub}h, and @{b}No Line@{ub}).

	The @{b}w@{ub} line value is the current line weight in points.

	The @{b}=@{ub} line value displays numeric values entered from the
keyboard.  These values can be passed to appropriate functions with their
respective hotkeys.  For instance, entering "2" then the letter "w" will set
the line weight to two points.  Entering "6" then the "[" key will set the
fill color to Blue (presuming the default ProVector palette).  This shortcut
is available with all of the other attribute keys, as well as "r" (@{b}Rotate@{ub})
and "s" (@{b}Scale@{ub}).

	Pressing the @{b}Esc@{ub} (Escape) key will clear an incorrect value entered
on the @{b}=@{ub} line.

	See @{" Hotkeys " link Hotkeys} for more information on the various hotkeys for
changing object attributes.

	Use the @{b}F2@{ub} Function Key to open and close the Status window.

@ENDNODE


